OL,6,FDr Dafydd Trystan, Chair of the Active
OL,7,FTravel Board, said: "As I travel
OL,8,Finternationally both within these
OL,9,Fislands and beyond, the work of Welsh
OL,10,FGovernment on active travel is
OL,11,Frecognised and celebrated as an
OL,12,Fexample of good practice. Yet, our
OL,13,Freport presents a mixed picture. "
OL,15,FHe said that there had been
OL,16,F"significant progress" in terms of
OL,17,Finvestment in active travel
OL,18,Finfrastructure, but that more data was
OL,19,Fneeded to identify changes in
OL,20,Fbehaviour "at a more granular level."
